exampleDescription: `DefaultImport` is the default export of the entry
`DefaultImport` is the default export of a module which is directly re-exported from the entry
`DefaultImport` is the default export of a module which is first imported then re-exported by the entry
`DefaultImport` is the default export of a module which is first imported using `import { default as DefaultImport }` then re-exported by the entry
`MixedDefault` is default-imported from another module and `MixedImportNamed` is an entity imported from that same module.
`NamedExportOne` is imported from an entry. In this entry file, `NamedExportOne` is directly exported via `{ NamedExportOne }` from another module

`NamedExportOne` is imported from an entry. In this entry file, `NamedExportOne` is directly imported via `{ NamedExportOne }` from another module and then reexported using a simple `export { NamedExportOne }` statement.

`AliasedNamedExportOne` is imported from an entry. In this entry file, `AliasedNamedExportOne` is imported via `{ NamedExportOne as AliasedNamedExportOne }` from another module and then reexported using a simple `export { NamedExportOne as NamedExportOneDupe }` statement.

`AliasedNamedExportOne` is imported from an entry. In this entry file, `AliasedNamedExportOne` is imported via `{ NamedExportOne as AliasedNamedExportOne }` from another module and then reexported using a simple `export { AliasedNamedExportOne }` statement.
`NamedExportOne` is imported from an entry. In this entry file, `NamedExportOne` is re-exported via wildcard from another module which is listed as a target.

`NamedExportOne` is imported from an entry. In this entry file, `NamedExportOne` is re-exported via wildcard from another module. In that module, `NamedExportOne` is also re-exported via wildcard from a third module. In this example, all modules are listed as targets.
`NamedExportOne` is imported from an entry. In this entry file, `NamedExportOne` is re-exported via wildcard from another module which is not listed as a target

`NamedExportOne` is imported from an entry. In this entry file, `NamedExportOne` is re-exported via wildcard from another module. In that module, `NamedExportOne` is also re-exported via wildcard from a third module. In this example, two last modules not listed as targets.
`NamedExports` is imported from an entry. In this entry file, `NamedExports` is first imported via wildcard from another module and then reexported using a simple `export { NamedExports }` statement.

`NamedExports` is imported from an entry. In this entry file, `NamedExports` is implicitly exported via a wildcard export from another module. In that module, `NamedExports` is first imported via wildcard from a third module and then reexported using a simple `export { NamedExports }` statement.
